Non - aligned states concerned over U . S . Iraq raids . Information ministers of non - aligned countries meeting in the Nigerian capital on Friday voiced concern over United States missile attacks on Iraq . " ( The countries ) expressed deep concern over the adverse effect ( the attacks ) are likely to have on peace and security in the region and further expressed their support for the people of Iraq , " a statement from the conference said . Iraq ' s information minister on Tuesday called on the non - aligned countries for support . The United States fired cruise missiles at Iraq on Tuesday and Wednesday after Iraqi troops helped a Kurdish faction seize a city in northern Iraq from a rival group on Saturday . Non - aligned information ministers have been meeting in Nigeria this week to discuss the imbalance of information between their countries and the developed world . 
